HEADWORD: ascot
<hw>ascot</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[from the fashionable clothjing worn
at the <etsep>Ascot</etsep> races.]</ety> <def>a cravat with wide square
ends, tied so that the ends are laid flat; the ends are often secured
with an ornamental pin; -- called <altname>cravat</altname> in
Britain.</def>⟦br⟧
